==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Significavit
<hw>Sig`ni*fi*ca"vit</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., (he)
has signified, perf. ind. of <ets>significare</ets> to signify.]</ety>
<fld>(Eng. Eccl. Law)</fld> <def>Formerly, a writ issuing out of
chancery, upon certificate given by the ordinary, of a man's standing
excommunicate by the space of forty days, for the laying him up in
prison till he submit himself to the authority of the church.</def>
<rj><au>Crabb.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Signify</ent>⟦br⟧
